  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min to prep, so get your casserole dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with foil</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-chilli-and-miso-pork-udon-noodles/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based, <strong>hob-safe</strong> <strong>oven-proof casserole dish </strong>with a matching lid with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-chilli-and-miso-pork-udon-noodles/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once hot, add your<strong> pork mince</strong> (remove the paper if required!) to the dish with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a stir for 2-3 min, breaking the pork mince up into rough, large pieces with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-chilli-and-miso-pork-udon-noodles/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Top, tail, peel and slice your <strong>carrot[s]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>into discs</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong> into wedges</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-chilli-and-miso-pork-udon-noodles/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>carrot discs </strong>and <strong>onion wedges </strong>to the dish with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong>, 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes</strong>,<strong> sambal </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>miso </strong>and <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up then add 400ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[520ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[680ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil, then cover with a lid and put the dish in the oven for an initial 20 min</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-chilli-and-miso-pork-udon-noodles/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-chilli-and-miso-pork-udon-noodles/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>After the initial 20 min, remove the dish from the oven and add your <strong>udon noodles</strong></p><p>Tip: Gently separate the noodles with a fork!</p><p>Cover with a lid and return the dish to the oven for 5-7 min further or until the noodles are tender and the pork is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>one pot chilli & miso pork udon noodles</strong></p><p>Trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-chilli-and-miso-pork-udon-noodles/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>To serve, top the<strong> one pot chilli & miso pork udon noodles </strong>with the<strong> sliced spring onion </strong>and<strong> crispy onions</strong></p><p>Dig in!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
